Ranger had the best accuracy out of all the models ran.

library(ranger)
ranger_model = ranger(is_fraud ~ amt + BinaryGender + city_pop,
                      data = train,
                      num.trees = 500)
print(ranger_model)
## Ranger result

test_encoded = model.matrix(~ amt + BinaryGender + city_pop + state - 1, data = test)
test_dmatrix = xgb.DMatrix(data = as.matrix(test_encoded))
test_predictions = predict(xgbmodel, newdata = test_dmatrix)
xgbrmse = sqrt(mean((test$is_fraud - test_predictions)^2))
print(xgbrmse)
